{{Infobox Judo technique |name =Hane makikomi |image = Hane-makikomi.jpg |image_size = 175px |alt = |caption = |class = [[Nage-waza]] |sub_class = [[Sutemi-waza]] |grip = |back_up = |follow_up = |targets = |counter = |kodokan =Yes |romaji =Hane makikomi |japanese =跳巻込 |english =Springing wraparound }}{{nihongo|'''Hane Makikomi'''|跳巻込}} is one of the original 40 [[Throw (grappling)|throws]] of [[Judo]] as developed by [[Jigoro Kano]].<ref name="canon_judo">Mifune, Kyuzo: ''The Canon of Judo'', Kodansha International Ltd. (Tokyo) 2004, {{ISBN|4-7700-2979-9}}, p.</ref> It belongs to the fourth group, [[Judo Lists#Yonkyo|Yonkyo]], of the traditional throwing list, Gokyo (no waza), of Kodokan Judo. It is also part of the current 67 Throws of Kodokan Judo. It is classified as a side sacrifice technique, [[Judo technique|Yoko-sutemi]].
