'''Lars Uhre''' (born 18 April 1972) is the coach of the [[Denmark national badminton team|Danish national badminton team]].<ref name="uhre-portraet">{{cite web | url=http://badminton.dk/cms/default.aspx?clubid=3547&m=225689&cmsid=132&pageid=1997 | title=Månedens portræt: Lars Uhre | publisher=Badminton Danmark | date=February 3, 2011 | accessdate=August 2, 2012 | author=Dall, Anders}}</ref>
== Career == Graduated from the [[University of Copenhagen]] in 2002, Uhre has a [[bachelor's degree]] in [[sports science]] and [[English language|English]].<ref name="uhre-portraet"/> From 2001 to 2006, he acted as the [[Summer Olympic Games|olympic coach]] of the [[Finland|Finnish]] badminton team.<ref name="uhre-portraet"/> From 2006 to 2010, he was the assistant national coach of the Danish national team.<ref name="uhre-portraet"/> In August 2010, he was promoted to coach of the Danish national team.<ref name="uhre-portraet"/>
