The '''Loto-Tonga Soka Centre''' is a [[Association football|football]] facility in [[Nukuʻalofa]], [[Tonga]]. It was funded by [[FIFA]] through the world football body's Goal Programme and was opened in 2001. It hosted matches of the [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification – OFC First Round|first round of the OFC 2018 FIFA World Cup qualifiers.]]<ref>{{cite news|title=History-making Cook Islands and Samoa open brightly|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/news/y=2015/m=8/news=history-making-cook-islands-and-samoa-open-brightly-2674199.html|accessdate=31 August 2015|publisher=FIFA|date=31 August 2015}}</ref> The main office of the [[Tonga Football Association]] is also located within the venue.<ref>{{cite web|title=Contact|url=http://www.tongafootball.to/tabid/1238/language/en-US/Default.aspx|publisher=Tonga Football Association|accessdate=31 August 2015}}</ref>
