[[Image:PalaisdesSportsdeBeaulieu-Nantes1.jpg|thumb|right|300px|Palais des Sports de Beaulieu in 2011]]

'''Palais des Sports de Beaulieu''' is an [[indoor arena|indoor sporting arena]] located in [[Nantes]], France. Built in 1973,<ref>[http://www.nantes.maville.com/Le-Palais-des-sports-de-Beaulieu-prend-l-eau-/re/actudet/actu_loc-624780------_actu.html Le Palais des sports de Beaulieu prend l'eau ]</ref> the seating capacity of the arena is for 5,500 people. It is currently home to the [[Hermine Nantes Atlantique]] [[basketball]] team.
The arena hosted the [[1973–74 FIBA European Champions Cup|1974 European champions cup]] final in basketball in which [[Real Madrid Baloncesto|Real Madrid]] defeated [[Ignis Varese]] 84–82,<ref>[http://www.galeon.com/realmadridbasket/euroleague.htm 8 EUROLIGAS BALONCESTO (6 SUBCAMPEÓN) (EUROPEAN BASKETBALL CHAMPIONS CUP)]</ref><ref name="Champions Cup 1973-74">[http://www.linguasport.com/baloncesto/internacional/clubes/c1/C1_74.htm Champions Cup 1973-74]</ref> the [[EuroBasket 1983|1983 European basketball championship]] finals<ref name="XXIII European Championship (Nantes 1983)">[http://www.linguasport.com/baloncesto/internacional/eurobasket/1983_NANTES.htm XXIII European Championship (Nantes 1983)]</ref> and the [[1991–92 FIBA European Cup|1992 European Cup]] final in which [[Real Madrid Baloncesto|Real Madrid]] defeated [[P.A.O.K. BC|P.A.O.K. Thessaloniki]].<ref name="European Cup 1991-92">[http://www.linguasport.com/baloncesto/internacional/clubes/c2/C2_92.htm European Cup 1991-92]</ref>

