{{Refimprove|date=December 2017}} {{Infobox venue | name = | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = | caption = Prince Louis Rwagasore Stadium | fullname = | former_names = | location = [[Bujumbura]], [[Burundi]] | coordinates = {{coord|3|23|0.0|S|29|22|25.6|E}} | broke_ground = | built = | opened = | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = | scoreboard = | cost = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | capacity = 10,000<ref>[https://books.google.nl/books?id=CDl_AgAAQBAJ&pg=PA99&lpg=PA99&dq=Prince+Louis+Rwagasore+Stadium+10000&source=bl&ots=UWEfkMvOWr&sig=SX8aiakR2AoHePGFfmMYa7xWibk&hl=nl&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj2767_-pLNAhUMCMAKHXxLC0QQ6AEISjAI#v=onepage&q=Prince%20Louis%20Rwagasore%20Stadium%2010000&f=false Info] on [[Google Books]]</ref> | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | acreage = | tenants = }}
'''Prince Louis Rwagasore Stadium''' is a [[multi-purpose stadium]] in [[Bujumbura]], [[Burundi]]. It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches. The stadium holds 10,000. It is named after former Burundian prime minister and independence hero, [[Louis Rwagasore]].
