{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2014}} {{Malay name|Razimie|Ramlli}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Razimie Ramlli | fullname = Muhammad Razimie bin Ramlli | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1990|8|6|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Batang Mitus]], [[Brunei]] | height = {{convert|1.64|m|ftin|abbr=on}} | position = [[Forward (association football)|Striker]] | currentclub = [[MS ABDB]] | clubnumber = 24 | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 2015– | caps1 = 44| goals1 = 33| clubs1 = [[MS ABDB]] | nationalyears1= 2016– | nationalcaps1= 3 | nationalgoals1= 1 | nationalteam1= [[Brunei national football team|Brunei]] | nationalyears2= 2018 | nationalcaps2= 3 | nationalgoals2= 0 | nationalteam2= [[Brunei national under-21 football team|Brunei U21]] | club-update = 9 November 2018 | ntupdate = 11 September 2018 }}
[[Private (rank)|Soldadu]] '''Muhammad Razimie bin Ramlli''' (born 6 August 1990) is a [[Brunei]]an international [[football]]er who plays for [[MS ABDB]] and the [[Brunei national football team]] as a [[Striker (association football)|striker]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bt.com.bn/sports-national/2016/04/24/ms-abdb-clinch-6-1-win-continue-domination|title=MS ABDB clinch 6-1 win, continue domination|publisher=The Brunei Times|date=24 April 2016|deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160506055649/http://www.bt.com.bn/sports-national/2016/04/24/ms-abdb-clinch-6-1-win-continue-domination|archivedate=6 May 2016|accessdate=18 November 2016}}</ref>
==Club career==
Razimie is a soldier with the [[Royal Brunei Armed Forces]] who began playing with its [[MS ABDB|sports council's]] football department in 2015, scoring 12 goals in his debut season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bt.com.bn/sports-national/2015/07/06/ms-abdb-coach-confident-winning-dst-super-league|title=MS ABDB coach confident of winning DST Super League|publisher=The Brunei Times|date=31 May 2014|deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150711103755/http://www.bt.com.bn/sports-national/2015/07/06/ms-abdb-coach-confident-winning-dst-super-league|archivedate=11 July 2015|accessdate=18 November 2016}}</ref> He won the [[Brunei Super League]] twice in a row and also the 2015 [[Brunei FA Cup]].
On 29 September 2017, Razimie scored a hat-trick in the 4-1 win over title contenders [[Kota Ranger FC]], who were unbeaten before the match took place.<ref>{{cite web |title=MS ABDB SNAP KOTA RANGER’S UNBEATEN RUN|url=https://www.brusports.com/2017/09/30/ms-abdb-snap-kota-rangers-unbeaten-run/|date=30 September 2017|publisher=BruSports News|accessdate=2 October 2017}}</ref>
==International career== After another solid season in [[2016 Brunei Super League|2016]], Razimie was selected for the [[Brunei national football team|Brunei national team]] in October for the [[2016 AFF Suzuki Cup qualification]] matches and the [[2016 AFC Solidarity Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Brunei to ‘treat each match like final’|url=http://borneobulletin.com.bn/brunei-treat-match-like-final/|date=1 November 2016|publisher=Borneo Bulletin|accessdate=18 November 2016|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161105004003/http://borneobulletin.com.bn/brunei-treat-match-like-final/|archivedate=5 November 2016|df=dmy-all}}</ref> He, along with [[Baharin Hamidon]], was a surprise addition to the squad that usually relies heavily on [[Brunei DPMM FC]] and [[Tabuan Muda]] players. He made his debut on 21 October against [[Laos national football team|Laos]] and scored the final goal of the game in a 4-3 defeat.<ref>{{cite web |title=Laos 4-3 Brunei: Laos finish in second place|url=http://www.affsuzukicup.com/news/laos-4-3-brunei-laos-finish-in-second-place|date=21 October 2016|publisher=Asean Football Federation|accessdate=18 November 2016}}</ref> He made one further appearance at the Solidarity Cup held two weeks later in [[Malaysia]].
In April 2018, he was selected as an overage player for the [[Brunei national under-21 football team|Brunei under-21 team]] competing for the [[2018 Hassanal Bolkiah Trophy]] held in his home country.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hassanalbolkiahtrophy.gov.bn/team/brunei-darussalam/|title=BRU - 2018 Hassanal Bolkiah Trophy|publisher=Information Department, Prime Minister's Office of Brunei|date=|accessdate=18 April 2018}}</ref> He came on in the second half of the opening game which ended 0-1 against [[Timor-Leste national under-21 football team|Timor-Leste]]. Later that year, he appeared for the full national team as a second-half substitute in a 1-0 win against [[Timor-Leste national football team|Timor-Leste]] at the [[Hassanal Bolkiah National Stadium]] on 8 September.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tirto.id/piala-aff-2018-singkirkan-brunei-timor-leste-masuk-grup-indonesia-cXPT|title=Piala AFF 2018: Singkirkan Brunei, Timor Leste Masuk Grup Indonesia|publisher=tirto.id|date=8 September 2018|accessdate=11 September 2018}}</ref>
